commit.message:
display: Add wayland compatibility

This fixes the display labeler, mainly.

- Under wayland, the labels will be provided by Cinnamon
- Under x11, the built-in labeler is still used.
- Use static colors (this was generated by the old palette code).

wacom: Add "disabled" to stylus button actions.

Default causes the button to perform primary/secondary mouse
button emulation. There was no way to make them actually do
nothing.

commit.message:
network/net-device.c: net_device_get_valid_connections - don't
return early if there's no active connection.

This was part of a fix for #269 but seems no longer necessary
for that, and it was preventing the ethernet device switch from
being able to re-enable the network.

Fixes #311.
Fixes linuxmint/cinnamon#10873.

commit.message:
Fix build when the color panel is disabled.

A typo in the display panel's build was resulting in it using
the 'sizes' variable defined in the color panel, as its build
file was being processed first.

When the color panel is disabled, that variable is no longer
pre-defined, exposing the typo and breaking the build.

Fixes #309.
